condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, F.2 | Description :The Recipient shall furnish to the Association, as soon as available,but in any case not later than November 30 of each year, the annual work plans and budgets and Safeguard Documents referred to inSection I, F.1 of Schedule 2 for their review and approval. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, B.4 | Description :In order to ensure the timely carrying out of the audits referred toin Section II, B.3 of Schedule 2, the Recipient shall engage auditors for the purpose not later than five (5) months after theEffective Date in accordance with the provision of Section III of Schedule 2. | Due Date :30-Mar-2017

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, B.5 | Description :Without limitation to the provisions of paragraph 1 above, no laterthan three (3) months after the Effective Date, the Recipient shall ensure that the PCU's accounting software has been adapted forthe Project in a manner satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :31-Jan-2017

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, 1 | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than July 31 of each year, commencingJuly 31, 2011, review the Project Implementing Entity's updated financial projections and take all necessary measures, includingreadjustment of annual tariff as necessary to permit the restoration or maintenance of the Financial Equilibrium. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS
Finance Agreement :Section 5.01 (a) of FA | Description :Subsidiary Agreement has been executed on behalf of the Recipient and theProject Implementation Entity. | Due Date :10-Oct-2011
Finance Agreement :Section 5.01 (b) | Description :Project Implementation Manual and Manual of Procedures have been adapted for theProject. | Due Date :10-Oct-2011

Finance Agreement :Section I A.5 of Schedule 2 | Description :No later than 3 months after effectiveness, the Recipient hasrecruited a financial management specialist for the Project. | Due Date :10-Jan-2012
Finance Agreement :Section II B.3 of Schedule 2 to PA | Description :The PIE shall have recruited an external independent auditorto carry out financial audits. | Due Date :29-Feb-2012

Finance Agreement :Section II B.4 of Schedule 2 | Description :To ensure timely carrying out of audits, the Recipient shall engageauditors no later than 6 months after effectiveness. | Due Date :29-Feb-2012

Finance Agreement :Section II B.5 of Schedule 2 to PA | Description :No later than 3 months after effectiveness, the PIE shall havepurchased and installed an asset management software for the Project. | Due Date :10-Jan-2012

Finance Agreement :Section II B.5 of Schedule 2 | Description :No later than 3 months after effectiveness, the Recipient shallensure that the PCU's accounting software has been adapted for the Project. | Due Date :10-Jan-2012
Finance Agreement :Section IV B.1 (b) of Schedule 2 | Description :No withdrawal shall be made under category 2 until the serviceagreement has been entered into. | Due Date :10-Jan-2012

Finance Agreement :Section V (a) of Schedule 2 | Description :The Recipient shall take all necessary measures, including anynecessary water supply tariffs revisions, to allow the PIE to restore and thereafter maintain financial equilibrium. | Due Date:31-Dec-2012
